//@version=5
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Momentum — RSI 70 + 5/20 EMA cross + RSI oversold-recovery.  RUN ON 1D.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// RSI is only useful at the extremes; these fire the actionable ones. ALL fire
// at the DAILY CLOSE via alert.freq_once_per_bar_close — a CONFIRMED, towards-EOD
// signal (no intraday wobble) and, since a daily bar closes once, each fires AT
// MOST ONCE PER DAY PER STOCK. They are meant to be rare.
//
//   ▲ RSI70 (orange) — daily RSI(14) crosses ABOVE 70; a close above 70 can begin
//                      a parabolic run (MU → 85). Fired at the close = confirmed.
//   ▲ 5/20  (lime)   — daily 5 EMA crosses ABOVE the 20 EMA (Steve Burns) — often
//                      the start of a sustained up-move. Stop = the 20 EMA.
//   ▲ OS↑   (aqua)   — daily RSI closes in the 30–35 BUY ZONE: reclaimed 30 from
//                      below, or dipped/holding in 30–35 from above. NEVER below 30
//                      (the falling knife — RSI 29 is not a buy). Fires on the first
//                      close into the zone. Washed-out quality/mega caps mean-revert
//                      here. Sent as a BUY (not a notice) so it's prominent, not lost.
//
// Pine v5: single-line alert() payloads matching the backend schema. NOTE: bind
// this on a DAILY (1D) chart so the alerts are daily-close events.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
indicator("Momentum — RSI 70 / 5-20 cross / oversold-recovery", "Momentum", overlay = true, max_labels_count = 100)

fire      = input.bool(true,  "Fire alerts")
show_ma   = input.bool(true,  "Plot 5 / 20 EMA")
os_floor = input.float(30.0, "Oversold zone FLOOR — NEVER buy below this RSI (knife)", minval = 20.0, maxval = 35.0, step = 1.0)
os_ceil  = input.float(35.0, "Oversold zone CEILING — RSI at/under this is the buy zone", minval = 30.0, maxval = 45.0, step = 1.0)

r   = ta.rsi(close, 14)
e5  = ta.ema(close, 5)
e20 = ta.ema(close, 20)
rsi70   = ta.crossover(r, 70.0)
cross   = ta.crossover(e5, e20)
// In the buy zone = RSI in [floor, ceil]. Fire on the FIRST daily close into it —
// which is exactly "reclaimed 30 from below" OR "dipped/holding in 30–35 from
// above"; never while RSI < 30 (the falling knife). Once per entry = rare.
in_zone    = (r >= os_floor) and (r <= os_ceil)
os_recover = in_zone and not in_zone[1]

if fire and rsi70
    pr = '{"symbol":"' + syminfo.ticker + '","price":"' + str.tostring(close, format.mintick) + '","rule":"rsi_70","direction":"BUY","interval":"D","entry":"' + str.tostring(close, format.mintick) + '","note":"RSI 70 — daily close pushed RSI above 70; a close above 70 can begin a parabolic run","fired_at":"' + str.tostring(timenow) + '"}'
    alert(pr, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
if fire and cross
    pc = '{"symbol":"' + syminfo.ticker + '","price":"' + str.tostring(close, format.mintick) + '","rule":"ema_5_20_cross","direction":"BUY","interval":"D","entry":"' + str.tostring(close, format.mintick) + '","stop":"' + str.tostring(e20, format.mintick) + '","note":"5/20 EMA bullish cross (Steve Burns) — daily 5 EMA crossed above the 20. STOP = 5/20 cross-under at the close (~20 EMA). Target = RSI 70","fired_at":"' + str.tostring(timenow) + '"}'
    alert(pc, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
if fire and os_recover
    po = '{"symbol":"' + syminfo.ticker + '","price":"' + str.tostring(close, format.mintick) + '","rule":"rsi_oversold","direction":"BUY","interval":"D","entry":"' + str.tostring(close, format.mintick) + '","note":"RSI oversold buy zone — daily RSI in 30-35 (reclaim/hold, never below 30). T1 = RSI 50, T2 = RSI 70. STOP = daily close back under RSI 30 (the NFLX stop-out)","fired_at":"' + str.tostring(timenow) + '"}'
    alert(po, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)

plot(show_ma ? e5  : na, "EMA 5",  color = color.new(color.yellow, 0), linewidth = 2)
plot(show_ma ? e20 : na, "EMA 20", color = color.new(color.green, 0),  linewidth = 2)
plotshape(rsi70,      title = "RSI70", style = shape.triangleup, location = location.belowbar, color = color.new(color.orange, 0), text = "RSI70", size = size.small)
plotshape(cross,      title = "5x20",  style = shape.triangleup, location = location.belowbar, color = color.new(color.lime, 0),   text = "5/20",  size = size.small)
plotshape(os_recover, title = "OS",    style = shape.triangleup, location = location.belowbar, color = color.new(color.aqua, 0),   text = "OS↑",   size = size.small)
